            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.21944/2603.21944v1/fig/fig_main.jpg",
                "caption": "Figure 2:The overview of Group3D.\nGiven multi-view RGB images, an MLLM predicts object categories across views,\nwhich are aggregated into aScene Vocabulary Memory.\nCategory-aware masks are lifted into 3D to construct a3D Fragment Memory.\nThe MLLM then organizes the vocabulary into semantic compatibility groups,\nwhich gate fragment merging together with geometric consistency to produce\nthe final open-vocabulary 3D object instances. Finally, multi-view evidence is accumulated to determine the final open-vocabulary category and 3D bounding box for each object instance.",
